# WHAT IT IS
#   TeleIRC is "a Go implementation of a Telegram â‡„ IRC bridge for
#   use with any IRC channel and any Telegram group/supergroup/
#   channel".  The daemon connects simultaneously to a Telegram
#   bot account (via the canonical go-telegram-bot-api library)
#   and an IRC server, then relays each Telegram message, sticker,
#   photo (via Imgur), GIF, voice note, audio file, video, video
#   note, document, location, contact, poll, dice, and edited
#   message into the configured IRC channel â€” and vice versa.
#   Configuration is `.env`-style;  the bot tracks bridge state
#   in memory and exits cleanly on SIGINT / SIGTERM.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from cmd/teleirc.go top-level
#                       `flag.String` / `flag.Bool` declarations â€”
#                       TeleIRC uses Go's stdlib `flag` package,
#                       not cobra or urfave/cli)
#   teleirc [OPTIONS]
#
#   Options:
#     -conf <FILE>                   Path to the config file
#                                    [default: .env]
#     -debug                         Enable debugging output
#     -version                       Print the current TeleIRC
#                                    version and exit
#
#   Standard Go flag-package conventions:
#     -h, --help                     Show help (auto-generated)
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `github.com/go-telegram-bot-api/
#   telegram-bot-api v4.6.4+incompatible` declared in go.mod â€”
#   `go-telegram-bot-api/telegram-bot-api` is THE canonical Go
#   Telegram Bot API binding maintained by Syfaro
#   (go-telegram-bot-api/telegram-bot-api, 6K+ stars, the Go
#   counterpart of python-telegram-bot / teloxide /
#   node-telegram-bot-api).  It exposes the
#   `tgbotapi.BotAPI` HTTP client constructor
#   (`NewBotAPI(token)`), the `tgbotapi.UpdatesChannel` polling
#   loop (`GetUpdatesChan(UpdateConfig{Offset, Timeout})`), the
#   complete Bot API typed model surface (`Update`, `Message`,
#   `User`, `Chat`, `MessageEntity`, `CallbackQuery`,
#   `InlineQuery`, `ChosenInlineResult`, `Audio`, `Document`,
#   `PhotoSize`, `Sticker`, `Video`, `Voice`, `VideoNote`,
#   `Contact`, `Location`, `Venue`, `Animation`, `Game`, `Poll`,
#   `Dice`, `ChatMemberUpdated`, `ChatJoinRequest`), the typed
#   `Config` request builders (`MessageConfig`, `PhotoConfig`,
#   `AudioConfig`, `DocumentConfig`, `VideoConfig`,
#   `AnimationConfig`, `EditMessageTextConfig`,
#   `EditMessageCaptionConfig`, `EditMessageReplyMarkupConfig`,
#   `DeleteMessageConfig`, `KickChatMemberConfig`,
#   `BanChatMemberConfig`, `RestrictChatMemberConfig`,
#   `PromoteChatMemberConfig`), and the Bot API webhook flow
#   (`SetWebhook`, `RemoveWebhook`, `ListenForWebhook`).
#   TeleIRC's `internal/handlers/telegram/client.go` constructs
#   `tgbotapi.NewBotAPI(settings.Telegram.Token)`, opens
#   `bot.GetUpdatesChan(...)`, and dispatches each `Update.
#   Message` into the IRC handler;  conversely, the IRC handler
#   marshals every IRC line into a `tgbotapi.NewMessage(chatID,
#   text)` send.  Verified via:
